cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper focuses on understanding scientific figures and their captions, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also mentions the use of knowledge graphs, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves training visual and language networks without supervision, which is a common topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
